QUANTITATIVE ANALYSIS

The dominant speeies of an assemblage may be said to include both those spe- cies whose remains are most abundant and those whose remains are most persistently present at the various horizons within the deposit. The most useful results of quantitative studies are obtained from localities where several thousand specimens can be collected.¹ Unfortunately‚ none of the localities in the Lance Creek area has yielded more than 280 specimens. F ailure to secure large collections is a result of the limited extent, both horizontally and vertically, of the lenticular beds containing the plant remains.
